message: Focus on the 'cooked' feature and aim for combinations of '1 vegetable + 2 protein' or '2 vegetable + 1 protein'. Always use the 'stove' to cook raw proteins (beef, beans, bacon, fish) first. Once you have your cooked proteins and vegetables, combine the two similar items first (e.g., 2 cooked proteins together, or 2 vegetables together) and then combine that result with the remaining component. This strategy consistently yielded items with values of 40 or 60. Avoid adding grains like wheat or tortilla to these primary cooked combinations; they often don't improve the score and might even reduce it, especially if the previous player said 'never add tortilla and wheat together'.
